{
    "_comment": [
        "Data configuration for 10_Merge Oversegmentation GNN.ipynb.",
        "Mirrors microsam_finetune_data.json: one file per channel under `image`,",
        "`label` is the ground-truth whole-cell instance map, and `correct_DIC_shift`",
        "is applied only to files with DIC in the name.",
        "Two keys are extra, because the merge task needs them:",
        "  `ais`       - micro-SAM AIS instance label map; these are the graph nodes. Required.",
        "  `embedding` - saved micro-sam tiled embedding store (.zarr) for the visual branch.",
        "Every channel listed under `image` is summed into the intensity image that",
        "drives the node/edge intensity features, so list only channels carrying signal.",
        "Leave `label` empty to build a graph with no training labels (inference only);",
        "leave `embedding` empty to train without visual features.",
        "  `cell_type` - per-image rule typing each GT cell: {\"all\": \"hyphal\"} for images with",
        "                only one cell type, else {\"metric\": ..., \"threshold\": ...} in px.",
        "                Per-image because magnification differs; see the design spec."
